00:00:07.642 --> 00:00:09.276 position:30% line:83% align:start
-What?
-This is crazy!

00:00:09.309 --> 00:00:11.613 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Is this for real?
-There's no way!

00:00:11.646 --> 00:00:13.113 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Who's that?
-What?

00:00:13.146 --> 00:00:14.949 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Toman Member] What the hell
is that Valhalla bastard

00:00:14.983 --> 00:00:16.584 position:16% line:89% align:start
doing at a Toman meeting?

00:00:16.618 --> 00:00:17.417 position:27% line:89% align:start
(crowd murmuring)

00:00:17.451 --> 00:00:19.086 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Chifuyu and Hanma?

00:00:19.954 --> 00:00:21.321 position:10% line:89% align:start
What's going on here, Mikey?

00:00:22.757 --> 00:00:25.927 position:19% line:83% align:start
As you all know, in the
Bloody Halloween battle,

00:00:25.960 --> 00:00:29.631 position:24% line:83% align:start
Valhalla had 300
men to Toman's 150.

00:00:29.664 --> 00:00:32.901 position:5% line:83% align:start
And, despite those odds, because
all of you did your best,

00:00:32.934 --> 00:00:35.269 position:27% line:83% align:start
we still managed
to claim victory!

00:00:35.302 --> 00:00:39.507 position:7% line:83% align:start
And now Vice Commander Hanma
has something he wants to say!

00:00:39.541 --> 00:00:42.744 position:21% line:89% align:start
(footsteps thudding)

00:00:42.777 --> 00:00:44.812 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'm Hanma Shuji from Valhalla.

00:00:44.846 --> 00:00:46.313 position:27% line:89% align:start
(crowd grumbling)

00:00:46.346 --> 00:00:49.383 position:10% line:83% align:start
Valhalla hasn't had an actual
commander for a long time.

00:00:49.416 --> 00:00:52.887 position:10% line:83% align:start
So, after losing this
battle, we have, as a group,

00:00:52.921 --> 00:00:55.023 position:21% line:83% align:start
decided to reorganize
under Toman.

00:00:55.055 --> 00:00:56.758 position:27% line:83% align:start
-What?
-There's no way!

00:00:56.791 --> 00:00:58.693 position:27% line:83% align:start
Valhalla and the
Tokyo Manji Gang

00:00:58.726 --> 00:01:00.528 position:13% line:89% align:start
are now officially allies!

00:01:00.562 --> 00:01:01.729 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Huh?

00:01:01.763 --> 00:01:02.730 position:30% line:83% align:start
-This is crazy!
-No way!

00:01:02.764 --> 00:01:04.231 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Toman Member] What?

00:01:04.264 --> 00:01:06.834 position:7% line:83% align:start
So all 300 members of Valhalla
are going to be under Toman?

00:01:06.868 --> 00:01:09.169 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Toman Member] That means
Toman's gonna have 450 members!

00:01:09.202 --> 00:01:11.171 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Toman Member] Dude,
Toman's gonna be awesome!

00:01:11.204 --> 00:01:12.507 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Toman] Yeah, unbeatable!

00:01:12.540 --> 00:01:13.608 position:21% line:89% align:start
I can't get over it!

00:01:13.641 --> 00:01:15.610 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Cheering Toman
Member] Toman rules!

00:01:15.643 --> 00:01:19.313 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Crowd] Toman, Toman,
Toman, Toman, Toman!

00:01:20.682 --> 00:01:22.115 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Hey, wait a sec!

00:01:22.149 --> 00:01:25.853 position:27% line:83% align:start
-(air whooshing)
-(tense music)

00:01:25.887 --> 00:01:28.488 position:16% line:83% align:start
-Toman, Toman!
-Something's wrong here!

00:01:28.523 --> 00:01:32.727 position:13% line:83% align:start
We finally managed to avoid
having Mikey kill Kazutora.

00:01:32.760 --> 00:01:35.362 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Toman, Toman!
-But now,

00:01:35.395 --> 00:01:37.197 position:24% line:83% align:start
if this dude joins
up with Toman,

00:01:37.230 --> 00:01:40.802 position:16% line:83% align:start
and then Toman and
Valhalla combine forces,

00:01:40.835 --> 00:01:41.869 position:27% line:83% align:start
-it's gonna mean-
-Toman!

00:01:41.903 --> 00:01:44.137 position:21% line:83% align:start
-So!
-(Takemichi gasping)

00:01:44.171 --> 00:01:46.473 position:13% line:83% align:start
Now for the guy who brought
Mikey and me together.

00:01:48.108 --> 00:01:50.377 position:16% line:83% align:start
It's only because of him
that this all worked out.

00:01:50.410 --> 00:01:52.714 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] (gasping) No way!

00:01:52.747 --> 00:01:54.214 position:24% line:89% align:start
So come on up here!

00:01:54.247 --> 00:01:55.750 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-What?

00:01:55.783 --> 00:01:56.784 position:24% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi gasping)

00:01:56.818 --> 00:01:57.919 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Oh no!

00:01:57.952 --> 00:01:59.587 position:35% line:83% align:start
-What?
-What, huh?

00:01:59.621 --> 00:02:00.655 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Hanma] Tetta Kisaki!

00:02:00.688 --> 00:02:01.656 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Crowd] Whoa!

00:02:01.689 --> 00:02:03.725 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Kisaki!

00:02:03.758 --> 00:02:05.793 position:21% line:89% align:start
Kisaki is the enemy.

00:02:05.827 --> 00:02:08.161 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Whoa!
-Yeah, yeah!

00:02:08.195 --> 00:02:09.998 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Yeah! (laughing)
-Hey!

00:02:10.031 --> 00:02:11.699 position:24% line:83% align:start
-How are you, man?
-Wow!

00:02:11.733 --> 00:02:12.900 position:30% line:83% align:start
-That's right!
-Yeah!

00:02:12.934 --> 00:02:14.002 position:16% line:83% align:start
-Yeah!
-(Toman member laughing)

00:02:14.035 --> 00:02:15.003 position:24% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi gasping)

00:02:15.036 --> 00:02:17.404 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Woo-hoo, yeah!
-Yeah!

00:02:17.437 --> 00:02:22.442 position:10% line:83% align:start
-(Takemichi hyperventilating)
-(somber music)

00:02:23.111 --> 00:02:26.380 position:27% line:89% align:start
(crowd cheering)

00:02:26.413 --> 00:02:29.917 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Takemichi] We're
gonna get taken over!

00:02:29.951 --> 00:02:35.155 position:10% line:83% align:start
-(singer singing in Japanese)
-(opening theme music)

00:04:00.074 --> 00:04:04.879 position:27% line:5% align:start
-(crowd cheering)
-(crowd laughing)

00:04:07.648 --> 00:04:10.283 position:21% line:83% align:start
Baji sacrificed his
life to protect Toman

00:04:10.317 --> 00:04:12.553 position:21% line:83% align:start
and now Kisaki's just
gonna take it over!

00:04:13.888 --> 00:04:15.189 position:13% line:89% align:start
That means, in the future,

00:04:15.223 --> 00:04:17.324 position:24% line:83% align:start
Toman's still going
to end up evil!

00:04:18.159 --> 00:04:20.228 position:16% line:83% align:start
-Did I mess it up again?
-Toman, Toman!

00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:22.196 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Mikey] There's one more
thing I'd like to say!

00:04:22.230 --> 00:04:23.798 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-Toman!

00:04:23.831 --> 00:04:26.466 position:16% line:83% align:start
We gained some things
at the Bloody Halloween,

00:04:26.501 --> 00:04:28.468 position:10% line:89% align:start
but we lost some things too.

00:04:29.670 --> 00:04:33.908 position:13% line:83% align:start
Our First Division Captain,
Keisuke Baji, is dead.

00:04:37.410 --> 00:04:40.214 position:16% line:83% align:start
I urge you all to deeply
reflect upon this truth

00:04:40.248 --> 00:04:41.949 position:10% line:89% align:start
and find a way to accept it.

00:04:42.984 --> 00:04:44.585 position:13% line:89% align:start
I leave the closing to you,

00:04:44.619 --> 00:04:47.955 position:16% line:83% align:start
First Division Vice
Captain Chifuyu Matsuno.

00:04:52.459 --> 00:04:54.294 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Chifuyu.

00:04:55.930 --> 00:04:58.331 position:16% line:83% align:start
I was seriously thinking
about quitting Toman,

00:04:59.499 --> 00:05:01.434 position:19% line:83% align:start
but then the commander
said this to me.

00:05:02.469 --> 00:05:04.371 position:27% line:83% align:start
"Are you going to
blow out the flame

00:05:04.404 --> 00:05:06.073 position:24% line:83% align:start
"of the First
Division for good?"

00:05:06.107 --> 00:05:07.875 position:21% line:89% align:start
(gentle somber music)

00:05:07.909 --> 00:05:09.342 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] You poor guy,

00:05:09.376 --> 00:05:12.547 position:19% line:83% align:start
this must be harder for
you than for anyone.

00:05:12.580 --> 00:05:15.850 position:5% line:83% align:start
Taking over as the First
Division Captain in Baji's place

00:05:15.883 --> 00:05:18.252 position:19% line:83% align:start
would have been way too
much for me to handle,

00:05:18.286 --> 00:05:20.221 position:7% line:89% align:start
so I talked with the commander.

00:05:20.254 --> 00:05:23.057 position:24% line:83% align:start
We talked for days
and days, in fact,

00:05:23.090 --> 00:05:24.725 position:24% line:83% align:start
and I finally came
to a conclusion.

00:05:26.493 --> 00:05:29.931 position:7% line:83% align:start
I'm the one who gets to decide
who I'm willing to follow!

00:05:30.998 --> 00:05:32.700 position:24% line:89% align:start
Takemichi Hanagaki!

00:05:32.733 --> 00:05:34.936 position:24% line:83% align:start
You're gonna take
over as the captain

00:05:34.969 --> 00:05:37.004 position:19% line:83% align:start
-of the First Division!
-(Takemichi gasping)

00:05:37.038 --> 00:05:38.539 position:35% line:83% align:start
-What?
-That guy?

00:05:38.573 --> 00:05:40.608 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Toman Member] Is that the guy
who always got his ass kicked?

00:05:40.641 --> 00:05:41.876 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Toman Member] Oh, I don't know.

00:05:41.909 --> 00:05:44.477 position:27% line:89% align:start
But this is nuts!

00:05:44.512 --> 00:05:47.347 position:19% line:83% align:start
So, Takemitchy, we will
honor Baji's final wish

00:05:47.380 --> 00:05:49.183 position:30% line:89% align:start
before he died.

00:05:49.217 --> 00:05:50.952 position:7% line:89% align:start
You are the one that Baji chose

00:05:50.985 --> 00:05:53.287 position:21% line:83% align:start
and the commander and
I have finalized it!

00:05:53.321 --> 00:05:54.454 position:24% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi gasping)

00:05:54.487 --> 00:05:55.990 position:10% line:89% align:start
(crowd murmuring in surprise)

00:05:56.023 --> 00:05:57.357 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Are you serious?
-Him?

00:05:57.390 --> 00:05:59.193 position:16% line:83% align:start
-I don't know.
-I wouldn't have guessed.

00:05:59.227 --> 00:06:03.331 position:10% line:89% align:start
(crowd murmuring in surprise)

00:06:03.363 --> 00:06:05.333 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Takemichi Hanagaki!
-(Takemichi gasping)

00:06:05.365 --> 00:06:06.934 position:24% line:83% align:start
Raise your head
and greet everyone!

00:06:06.968 --> 00:06:08.569 position:24% line:89% align:start
(triumphant music)

00:06:08.603 --> 00:06:11.839 position:10% line:89% align:start
I just know you can save her!

00:06:12.673 --> 00:06:14.809 position:16% line:89% align:start
Save everyone if you can.

00:06:14.842 --> 00:06:15.843 position:41% line:89% align:start
Crybaby

00:06:16.777 --> 00:06:17.778 position:44% line:89% align:start
hero.

00:06:18.613 --> 00:06:19.780 position:21% line:89% align:start
This isn't over yet.

00:06:21.048 --> 00:06:22.516 position:10% line:89% align:start
I've got to take over Toman!

00:06:23.517 --> 00:06:25.987 position:16% line:89% align:start
I'm leaving them to you.

00:06:26.020 --> 00:06:30.091 position:7% line:89% align:start
(suspenseful triumphant music)

00:06:30.124 --> 00:06:32.159 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Hinata] Please, please go.

00:06:32.193 --> 00:06:35.529 position:5% line:83% align:start
You're so important to me, I
don't want you to die here too.

00:06:36.463 --> 00:06:38.032 position:21% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi grunting)

00:06:38.065 --> 00:06:40.433 position:13% line:89% align:start
This is still not over yet!

00:06:40.467 --> 00:06:42.570 position:7% line:83% align:start
-(crowd gasping)
-(crowd murmuring in surprise)

00:06:42.603 --> 00:06:44.105 position:16% line:89% align:start
I can still change Toman!

00:06:45.273 --> 00:06:46.240 position:41% line:89% align:start
I can!

00:06:46.274 --> 00:06:47.909 position:24% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi sobbing)

00:06:47.942 --> 00:06:49.409 position:24% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi gasping)

00:06:49.442 --> 00:06:51.779 position:5% line:89% align:start
Thanks for this one last chance!

00:06:51.812 --> 00:06:53.413 position:30% line:89% align:start
(pensive music)

00:06:53.446 --> 00:06:54.882 position:30% line:89% align:start
What the hell?

00:06:54.916 --> 00:06:56.217 position:16% line:89% align:start
What are you crying for?

00:06:56.250 --> 00:06:57.518 position:19% line:89% align:start
What a crazy reaction!

00:06:57.551 --> 00:07:00.554 position:16% line:83% align:start
Yeah, now I'm gonna have
to redo his embroidery.

00:07:00.588 --> 00:07:04.225 position:13% line:83% align:start
(chuckling) That's not
raising your head, dumbass.

00:07:04.258 --> 00:07:07.728 position:10% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi strained sobbing)

00:07:09.530 --> 00:07:12.099 position:21% line:83% align:start
-(footsteps thudding)
-(triumphant music)

00:07:12.133 --> 00:07:14.302 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takemichi] The more I do,
the worse the situation

00:07:14.335 --> 00:07:17.505 position:24% line:83% align:start
seems to get, but
there's still hope,

00:07:18.205 --> 00:07:20.041 position:33% line:89% align:start
right, Naoto?

00:07:21.342 --> 00:07:22.810 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Hinata] Huh?

00:07:22.843 --> 00:07:25.445 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takemichi] There has to be
something I can still do!

00:07:26.547 --> 00:07:28.015 position:30% line:89% align:start
(air whooshing)

00:07:28.049 --> 00:07:30.551 position:24% line:89% align:start
(energy crackling)

00:07:30.584 --> 00:07:33.688 position:30% line:89% align:start
(upbeat music)

00:07:33.721 --> 00:07:37.224 position:7% line:89% align:start
I came back to 2017 this time,

00:07:37.258 --> 00:07:40.127 position:7% line:89% align:start
back to the rental shop again.

00:07:40.161 --> 00:07:41.929 position:21% line:89% align:start
(footsteps thudding)

00:07:41.963 --> 00:07:42.964 position:35% line:89% align:start
My manager.

00:07:42.997 --> 00:07:45.566 position:24% line:83% align:start
Everything's just
the same as it was.

00:07:45.599 --> 00:07:48.002 position:27% line:83% align:start
So sorry to keep
you waiting, sir!

00:07:48.035 --> 00:07:48.936 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Huh?

00:07:48.970 --> 00:07:50.738 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Manager] I checked,
but I'm sorry to say

00:07:50.771 --> 00:07:53.407 position:10% line:83% align:start
we don't have what you're
looking for at this location.

00:07:53.441 --> 00:07:54.942 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Huh?

00:07:54.976 --> 00:07:55.776 position:38% line:89% align:start
What the?

00:07:56.644 --> 00:07:58.079 position:16% line:83% align:start
-I called around to the-
-What am I doing

00:07:58.112 --> 00:07:59.513 position:13% line:83% align:start
-with this nice watch?
-Other stores in the area,

00:07:59.547 --> 00:08:00.480 position:21% line:83% align:start
-but even there it's-
-And this expensive

00:08:00.514 --> 00:08:01.615 position:30% line:83% align:start
-looking bag?
-On back order,

00:08:01.649 --> 00:08:04.085 position:16% line:83% align:start
so it will take at least
a week to get it in.

00:08:04.118 --> 00:08:05.619 position:13% line:83% align:start
-What would you like to do?
-(Takemichi gasping)

00:08:05.653 --> 00:08:08.089 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Takemichi] What the
hell is this haircut?

00:08:08.122 --> 00:08:09.557 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Manager] Sir?

00:08:09.590 --> 00:08:12.026 position:13% line:83% align:start
Uh, I, uh, oh, that's
okay, don't worry about it!

00:08:13.427 --> 00:08:15.062 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Manager] Thank you, sir!

00:08:15.096 --> 00:08:17.264 position:24% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi gasping)

00:08:17.298 --> 00:08:19.700 position:5% line:89% align:start
Took you long enough, Takemichi.

00:08:19.734 --> 00:08:22.503 position:19% line:83% align:start
You love coming to this
rental shop, don't you?

00:08:23.237 --> 00:08:25.239 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Wait, who is this?

00:08:25.272 --> 00:08:26.440 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Let's go.
-(car horn blaring)

00:08:26.474 --> 00:08:28.075 position:19% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi shuddering)

00:08:28.109 --> 00:08:29.210 position:38% line:89% align:start
Go where?

00:08:29.243 --> 00:08:30.644 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Man] Get in already.

00:08:32.146 --> 00:08:33.247 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:08:33.280 --> 00:08:38.285 position:27% line:83% align:start
-(car whooshing)
-(tense music)

00:08:39.353 --> 00:08:40.621 position:10% line:89% align:start
I ended up getting in, but...

00:08:41.756 --> 00:08:44.425 position:21% line:83% align:start
So, uh, where
exactly are we going?

00:08:44.458 --> 00:08:46.460 position:27% line:83% align:start
Huh, the hell are
you talking about?

00:08:46.494 --> 00:08:47.895 position:13% line:89% align:start
We're going to your place.

00:08:47.928 --> 00:08:48.963 position:38% line:89% align:start
My place?

00:08:50.331 --> 00:08:51.632 position:5% line:89% align:start
Hold on, my apartment's actually

00:08:51.665 --> 00:08:53.467 position:10% line:83% align:start
-the other way-
-You gave the orders for this

00:08:53.502 --> 00:08:55.002 position:19% line:89% align:start
isn't that right, Koji?

00:08:55.036 --> 00:08:55.903 position:38% line:89% align:start
Yes, sir!

00:08:55.936 --> 00:08:57.571 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] I gave them orders?

00:08:57.605 --> 00:08:59.508 position:24% line:83% align:start
What the hell are
they talking about?

00:08:59.540 --> 00:09:01.442 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Koji] Would you mind
if I had a smoke, sir?

00:09:01.475 --> 00:09:02.843 position:21% line:83% align:start
-(Koji grunting)
-(Takemichi gasping)

00:09:02.877 --> 00:09:04.311 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Man] Takemichi doesn't like
cars that smell like smoke!

00:09:04.345 --> 00:09:05.514 position:33% line:89% align:start
What the hell

00:09:05.546 --> 00:09:06.914 position:16% line:83% align:start
-is going on here?
-I already told you that,

00:09:06.947 --> 00:09:08.282 position:10% line:83% align:start
-you jackass!
-They care about what I like?

00:09:08.315 --> 00:09:09.216 position:10% line:83% align:start
-Alright, alright, I'm sorry!
-Scary guys like these?

00:09:09.250 --> 00:09:10.551 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Koji] Holy smokes!

00:09:10.584 --> 00:09:11.886 position:21% line:83% align:start
-(Takemichi gasping)
-Was that a pun?

00:09:11.919 --> 00:09:12.553 position:13% line:83% align:start
-Are you making fun of me?
-I know, I'll call Naoto!

